      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It becomes disturbingly clear that your pain stems from deeply feeling cut off from others through this constant online presence. While the idea of stopping might feel liberating in that moment, it is crucial to remember that your worth and existence are not defined by digital footprints or the ability to maintain a fake connection. Even if the silence feels scary, reaching out to a trusted human being is a far stronger path to finding real peace than escaping into the unknown.",
